'''''The Year's Work in English Studies''''' was a journal published annually by the English Association. [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] contributed three review-essays for the section ''Philology: General Works''.<ref>{{CG|RG}}, p. 964 (entry "The Early English Text Society")</ref>

The first review-essay was published in the first issue of Volume IV for 1923 (published on [[8 January]] in [[1925]],<ref>{{CG|C}}, p. 128 (entry "8 January 1925")</ref> though the imprint date states 1924), pages 20–37.<ref>{{webcite|author=[[J.R.R. Tolkien]]|articleurl=http://ywes.oxfordjournals.org/content/IV/1/20.full.pdf+html|articlename=Philology: General Works (1923)|dated=01 September 1924|website=|accessed=}}</ref>

The second review-essay was published in the first issue of Volume 5 for 1924 (published in March of 1926), pages 26–65.<ref>{{webcite|author=[[J.R.R. Tolkien]]|articleurl=http://ywes.oxfordjournals.org/content/5/1/26.full.pdf+html|articlename=Philology: General Works (1924)|dated=|website=|accessed=}}</ref>

The third review-essay was published in the first issue of Volume VI for 1925 (published in February of 1927), pages 32–66.<ref>{{webcite|author=[[J.R.R. Tolkien]]|articleurl=http://ywes.oxfordjournals.org/content/VI/1/32.full.pdf+html|articlename=Philology: General Works (1925)|dated=|website=|accessed=}}</ref>

Tolkien wrote about writing the W sections for the [[Oxford English Dictionary]] as well as publications concerning names of places. Throughout the essays he attempted to inform the reader while including bits of humor to entertain.<ref>{{CG|RG}}, p. 1133 (entry "''The Year's Work in English Studies''")</ref>

